# Example .npmrc configuration for @stridetime packages
# Copy this file to .npmrc and replace ${GITHUB_TOKEN} with your actual token

@stridetime:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}

# To create a GitHub Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to GitHub Settings > Developer settings > Personal access tokens > Tokens (classic)
# 2. Click "Generate new token (classic)"
# 3. Give it a name like "stride-packages"
# 4. Select the "read:packages" scope (and "write:packages" if you need to publish)
# 5. Click "Generate token" and copy the token
# 6. Replace ${GITHUB_TOKEN} above with your actual token
# 7. Save this file as .npmrc (without the .example extension)
